{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:ephesians.5",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "ephesians",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Ephesians 5 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:1",
      "text": "Therefore be imitators of God, as beloved children.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:2",
      "text": "And walk in love, as Christ loved us and gave himself up for us, a fragrant offering and sacrifice to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:3",
      "text": "But fornication and all impurity or covetousness must not even be named among you, as is fitting among saints.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:4",
      "text": "Let there be no filthiness, nor silly talk, nor levity, which are not fitting; but instead let there be thanksgiving.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:5",
      "text": "Be sure of this, that no fornicator or impure man, or one who is covetous (that is, an idolater), has any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:6",
      "text": "Let no one deceive you with empty words, for it is because of these things that the wrath of God comes upon the sons of disobedience.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:7",
      "text": "Therefore do not associate with them,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:8",
      "text": "for once you were darkness, but now you are light in the Lord; walk as children of light",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:9",
      "text": "(for the fruit of light is found in all that is good and right and true),",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:10",
      "text": "and try to learn what is pleasing to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:11",
      "text": "Take no part in the unfruitful works of darkness, but instead expose them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:12",
      "text": "For it is a shame even to speak of the things that they do in secret;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:13",
      "text": "but when anything is exposed by the light it becomes visible, for anything that becomes visible is light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:14",
      "text": "Therefore it is said, “Awake, O sleeper, and arise from the dead, and Christ shall give you light.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:15",
      "text": "Look carefully then how you walk, not as unwise men but as wise,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:16",
      "text": "making the most of the time, because the days are evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:17",
      "text": "Therefore do not be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:18",
      "text": "And do not get drunk with wine, for that is debauchery; but be filled with the Spirit,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:19",
      "text": "addressing one another in psalms and hymns and spiritual songs, singing and making melody to the Lord with all your heart,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:20",
      "text": "always and for everything giving thanks in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ to God the Father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:21",
      "text": "Be subject to one another out of reverence for Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:22",
      "text": "Wives, be subject to your husbands, as to the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:23",
      "text": "For the husband is the head of the wife as Christ is the head of the church, his body, and is himself its Savior.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:24",
      "text": "As the church is subject to Christ, so let wives also be subject in everything to their husbands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:25",
      "text": "Husbands, love your wives, as Christ loved the church and gave himself up for her,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:26",
      "text": "that he might sanctify her, having cleansed her by the washing of water with the word,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:27",
      "text": "that he might present the church to himself in splendor, without spot or wrinkle or any such thing, that she might be holy and without blemish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:28",
      "text": "Even so husbands should love their wives as their own bodies. He who loves his wife loves himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:29",
      "text": "For no man ever hates his own flesh, but nourishes and cherishes it, as Christ does the church,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:30",
      "text": "because we are members of his body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:31",
      "text": "“For this reason a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and the two shall become one flesh.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:32",
      "text": "This mystery is a profound one, and I am saying that it refers to Christ and the church;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ephesians.5.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ephesians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Ephesians 5:33",
      "text": "however, let each one of you love his wife as himself, and let the wife see that she respects her husband.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
